9 An Act relating to health insurance; authorizing
health care provider to accept certain payments;
10 requiring application of certain charge to deductible
and maximum out-of-pocket expense; requiring health
11 benefit plan to establish certain procedure and
identify necessary documentation; requiring certain
12 information to be accessible on certain website;
prohibiting waiver of certain requirements; providing
13 for codification; and providing an effective date.
14
15
16 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
17 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
18 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 6046 of Title 36, unless there
19 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
20 A. A health care provider may not be prohibited by a health
21 benefit plan from accepting directly from an enrollee full payment
22 for a health care service in lieu of submitting a claim to the
23 enrollee’s health benefit plan. A health care provider’s discounted
