1 cash price for services rendered shall be considered full payment
2 for purposes of this section.
3 B. An enrollee’s health benefit plan shall apply the charge for
4 a health care service for which a health care provider accepts a
5 payment described in subsection A of this section from an enrollee
6 toward the enrollee’s deductible and annual maximum out-of-pocket
7 expense if the service is a medically necessary covered service
8 under the plan. Payments for uncovered services shall be ineligible
9 for application toward an enrollee’s deductible and annual maximum
10 out-of-pocket expense.
11 C. The enrollee’s health benefit plan shall:
12 1. Establish a procedure by which an enrollee may claim credit
13 for any expense under subsection B of this section; and
14 2. Identify documentation necessary to support a claim for a
15 credit under subsection B of this section.
16 D. Information about the procedure and documentation described
17 in subsection C of this section shall be readily accessible to the
18 enrollee on the health benefit plan’s website.
19 E. The requirements of this section shall not be waived,
20 voided, or nullified by contract.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
